This is a Research Paper RAG Assistant built by a Data Scientist learning production ML
engineering.
Stack: Python 3.11, LangChain, LangGraph, ChromaDB, OpenAI embeddings, Claude and GPT-4o
LLMs, Cohere reranker, RAGAS evaluation, Streamlit UI.
Machine: Apple M3 MacBook Air. Use device="mps" for any local PyTorch model. No Docker.
Code style: type hints on every function, a docstring explaining what and why, clear variable names.
The developer writes all code themselves. When helping, explain the concept — do not generate
whole files.
Always explain what a suggestion does before showing the code.
All LLM calls must go through src/generation/llm_router.py only.
ChromaDB must always use PersistentClient with a path — never in-memory.
Streamlit values that must survive a page rerun must use st.session_state.
